text.section:
Any board of education may obtain buildings for school purposes by proceeding under the provisions of KRS 162.120 to 162.290 utilizing a nonprofit finance corporation established pursuant to the provisions of KRS 273.161 to 273.390, inclusive, and KRS 58.180 as an issuing agency for the bonds instead of a city or county. When applied to such boards of education, KRS 162.120 to 162.290 shall be so read that the term:
"City" means a finance corporation acting as an agency and instrumentality of the board pursuant to KRS 58.180;
"City clerk" means the secretary of the finance corporation;
"Governing body of the city" means the board of directors of the finance corporation or other governing body thereof;
"Mayor" means president or chief executive officer of the finance corporation; and
"Ordinance" means an ordinance, resolution, or trust indenture or a similar document.
